  "text": "Problem (9) is in fact an optimal scheduling problem. E* is the least effort required in scheduling the removal of newly infecteds to achieve pathogen exclusion. E* therefore maintains a direct link between control and second generation infecteds. This optimal scheduling formulation can be advantageously compared with ways of handling external forcing that find alternative solutions to the time-dependency problem in second generation infection [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
